  "prompt": "What are symptoms of autism in kids?",
  "response": "Here are some common signs of autism in children:\n\nSocial Communication Symptoms:\n1. Limited eye contact\n2. Difficulty understanding social cues\n3. Challenges making or maintaining friendships\n4. Trouble sharing emotions or interests\n5. Limited or no verbal communication\n\nBehavioral Symptoms:\n1. Repetitive movements or behaviors\n2. Intense focus on specific interests\n3. Resistance to changes in routine\n4. Unusual reactions to sensory inputs\n5. Preference for playing alone\n\nCommunication Signs:\n1. Delayed speech development\n2. Speaking in unusual tones or patterns\n3. Difficulty understanding jokes or sarcasm\n4. Literal interpretation of language\n5. Trouble understanding non-verbal communication\n\nDevelopmental Indicators:\n1. Delayed developmental milestones\n2. Uneven skill development\n3. Difficulty with imaginative play\n4. Challenges with fine or gross motor skills\n\nImportant Notes:\n- Symptoms vary widely between individuals\n- Signs typically appear before age 3\n- Professional evaluation is essential for diagnosis\n- Early intervention can significantly help development\n\nIf concerned, consult a pediatrician or autism specialist for professional assessment.",
